condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Adoption of the Food Safety Law | Description :Effectiveness condition. | Due Date :10-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :Approval of sub-project applications. | Description :Withdrawal condition for sub-projects financed underSub-components 2.2 and 3.2. Approval of sub-project applications by the respective evaluation and selection committees. | Due Date:31-Dec-2014
Finance Agreement :Approval of the Grant Operational Manual | Description :Withdrawal condition for Sub-components 2.2 and 3.2. |Due Date :01-Jan-2013
Finance Agreement :Approval of the Project Operational Manual. | Description :Effectiveness condition. | Due Date :10-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :Section I.C of Schedule 2 | Description :Immediately upon the selection of a Sub-project pursuant to theeligibility criteria and procedures established in the GOM, the Recipient, through AIPA, shall provide a Matching Investment Grant(MIG) under a Sub–project Agreement to be entered into with the respective Beneficiary on terms and conditions approved by theAssociation and stipulated in the GOM. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

The Additional Conditions of Effectiveness consist of the following:(i) that the Project Operational Manual (“POM”) and the GrantOperational Manual (“GOM”) have been updated and adopted by the Recipient in a manner acceptable to the Bank, and(ii) that theAmendments have been executed and delivered and all conditions precedent to their effectiveness (other than the effectiveness ofthis Agreement) have been fulfilled.The Effectiveness Deadline is the date one hundred eighty (180) days after the SignatureDate.
